<section class="phase-page">

    <h1>Planning & Business Understanding</h1>

    <section class="phase-section">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>

        <p>
            Proofolio is a personal software engineering case study designed to showcase
            projects through the complete software development lifecycle rather than
            presenting only final results.
        </p>

        <p>
            The project focuses on demonstrating planning, analysis, design, development,
            testing, and documentation in a clear and structured way.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="phase-section">
        <h2>The Problem</h2>

        <div class="cards-container">
            <div class="info-card">
                <h3>Lack of Process Visibility</h3>
                <p>
                    Most portfolios only display the final interface without explaining
                    the development process behind the project.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h3>Missing Documentation</h3>
                <p>
                    Many projects do not include workflows, technical decisions, testing
                    evidence, or structured documentation.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h3>Limited Technical Evaluation</h3>
                <p>
                    Recruiters may struggle to evaluate the candidate’s actual technical
                    understanding from visual results alone.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="phase-section">
        <h2>The Vision</h2>

        <p>
            clearly present the full project journey from planning to implementation and testing.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="phase-section">
        <h2>Project Goals</h2>

        <ul class="goals-list">
            <li>Present projects through clear SDLC phases</li>
            <li>Demonstrate real software engineering workflows</li>
            <li>Showcase technical and analytical thinking</li>
            <li>Improve project presentation for recruiters and team leaders</li>
            <li>Build a structured and scalable portfolio system</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

</section>